Competition: South American Club Championship 
BlockSource: http://www.rsssf.com/sacups/copa48.html
Season: 1948

*Colo Colo (Chile)       - National champions of 1947 and hosts
*Emelec (Ecuador)        - apparently invited (no national championship)
*Lítoral (Bolivia)       - La Paz champions of 1947
*Municipal (Peru)        - National runners-up of 1947
*Nacional (Uruguay)      - National champions of 1947
*River Plate (Argentina) - National champions of 1947
*Vasco da Gama (Brazil)  - Rio de Janeiro champions of 1947 
*
*NB: CBD (the Brazilian FA) awarded the Brazilian berth to the 1947 Rio de Janeiro champions because Rio de Janeiro had won the 1946
*    Brazilian Championship of State Teams.

